<TITLE> 230 more BDR men arrested </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Feni, May 14 (bdnews24.com)Police have arrested another 230 border guards from Chittagong, Feni, Jessore and Kushtia since Wednesday night in the sedition case filed in connection with the Feb 25-26 bloodbath at BDR headquarters in Dhaka. Chittagong Satkania police detained 81 BDR men from Baitul Izzat BDR Training Centre on Thursday morning. They were arrested for the Feb 26 mutiny in the training centre, a day after the Peelkhana mutiny in the Peelkhana headquarters. Satkhania police chief Aslam Hossain told bdnews24.com the arrestees were being taken to Chittagong court. Aslam filed the case on Tuesday night against 500 BDR men with the Chittagong Judicial Magistrate's Court. Of the 500, the court issued arrest warrant against 100 people. The remaining 19 BDR members were taken under RAB custody for interrogation. Feni Dagonbhuiyan police chief Santosh Barua told bdnews24.com on Thursday morning that 64 BDR men were arrested from 19 Rifles Battalion headquarters at Jaylaskar. The arrestees were taken to the local judicial magistrate court-2 at 9:30am, he said. On the day after the Feb 25 Peelkhana mutiny, the men posted at Jaylaskar BDR camp broke the unit armoury, took out arms, fired shots in the air to create panic in the locality and barricaded the Feni-Maijdi road. Barua filed a case on Tuesday with the court, accusing 64 BDR men of armoury looting and hindering road traffic movement. Jessore Jessore police detained 43 BDR men from 22 Rifles Battalion at Jhumjhumpur. Additional police superintendent Zakir Hossain told bdnews24.com they were shown arrested in the case filed in connection with the Feb 26 BDR mutiny in Jessore. As the arrestees were produced before the court at around 10am, additional chief judicial magistrate Abdus Sabur Mina ordered them into jail. The court set May 21 for their next appearance. Kushtia Kushtia police on Thursday arrested 42 BDR members on charges of sedition. Police raided the Mirpur sector of the border forces at around 10am and arrested the 42 including deputy assistant director Shakhawat Hossain. They took them to Mirpur Police Station, Kushtia assistant police super Protyush Kumar Majumder said. Mirpur police chief Uttam Kumar Barua said the arrestees would be produced to the court after interrogation. bdnews24.
